tacle of blinding lights, sub bass and walls of cannon-fire percussion. They sound like the biggest bits of <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/music/arcadefire\">Arcade Fire</a>, <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/music/u2\">U2</a>, the <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/music/killers\">Killers</a> and <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/music/one-direction\">One Direction</a> put through a giant blender: rock music at heart, but with digital chart pop knobs on.</p> <p> Their songs so seamlessly blend together familiar lyrics – “Going back to my roots”, “Forever young” and so on – that they could have been put together by a bot program. And yet, amid the unsubtlety, meaning tiptoes into view. Catwalk-hogging singer Dan Reynolds makes a sincere speech about the refugee crisis, pointing out that 11 million people – half of them children – are homeless as a result of wars and revealing that a recent visit to a refugee camp reduced him to tears.</p>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"b2f29a1059f7edaef42da39fdf379f66e8f30fb2\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/b2f29a1059f7edaef42da39fdf379f66e8f30fb2/0_0_4842_3232/1000.jpg\" alt=\"Reynolds in more familiar mode.\" width=\"1000\" height=\"667\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\">Triumph through struggle … Reynolds in more familiar mode.</span> <span class=\"element-image__credit\">Photograph: Ian Hinchliffe/Rex Shutterstock</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <p> After several songs struggling with his voice, he tells the crowd that he suffers from <a href=\"http://www.nhs.uk/conditions/ankylosing-spondylitis/pages/introduction.aspx\">ankylosing spondylitis</a>, an autoimmune-type disease that will eventually turn him into “an old person at a young age”. </p> <p>Discussing his condition to “show support for others with chronic conditions” undoubtedly gives <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Rl3ELiPXFRo\">Gold</a> and <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w5tWYmIOWGk\">On Top of the World</a> – songs about triumph through struggle and loneliness at the top – a certain extra heft. By <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ktvTqknDobU\">Radioactive</a>, their mega-selling download, Reynolds can barely sing, but the audience sing his words. The exhausted American thanks “the most gracious crowd we ever played to”, and what began as a seemingly empty spectacle has ended up a moving example of “the show must go on”. </p> <ul> <li>At <a href=\"http://www.livenation.co.uk/artist/imagine-dragons-tickets\">Cardiff Arena</a> on 11 November. Box office: 029-2022 4488. <a href=\"https://www.imaginedragonsmusic.com/tour\">Then touring.</a><br /></li> </ul>","internalOctopusCode":"10969897","productionOffice":"UK","newspaperEditionDate":"2015-11-12T00:00:00Z","hasStoryPackage":"false","internalPageCode":"2405099","internalRevision":"421","internalContentCode":"458367072","publication":"The Guardian","trailText":"Tonight’s gig is showstopping for a different reason, as singer Dan Reynolds laments the refugee crisis and reveals the chronic illness he’s battling","allowUgc":"false","starRating":"3","headline":"Imagine Dragons review – stadium-rock spectacle tiptoes into meaning","byline":"Dave Simpson","isInappropriateForSponsorship":"false","commentable":"true","firstPublicationDate":"2015-11-11T12:06:14Z","thumbnail":"http://media.guim.co.uk/cf17820950151eefd82e3e58781bfe1cc81eed3e/0_134_3000_1801/140.jpg","isPremoderated":"false","internalComposerCode":"564316bfe4b08b339848c3e2","newspaperPageNumber":"46","commentCloseDate":"2015-12-11T00:00:00Z","standfirst":"<p><strong>Arena, Leeds</strong><br>Tonight’s gig is showstopping for a different reason, as singer Dan Reynolds laments the refugee crisis and reveals the chronic illness he’s battling</p>","creationDate":"2015-11-11T10:21:51Z","showInRelatedContent":"true","lastModified":"2015-11-11T22:00:25.655Z","legallySensitive":"false"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com