d just as the punters were starting to shake their shoulders. Tempus Fugit, a 1940s bebop classic by Corea’s early piano influence <a draggable=\"true\" href=\"http://www.allaboutjazz.com/the-amazing-bud-powell-black-genius-jazz-history-and-the-challenge-of-bebop-bud-powell-by-ian-patterson.php\">Bud Powell</a> unleashed a captivating stream of fresh melody from the leader, and a thrilling percussion climax of gleeful banter between Quintero and Gilmore. For the encore, Corea invited rising young British jazz star <a draggable=\"true\" href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/music/2015/jul/03/jacob-collier-review-ronnie-scotts-jazz-new-messiah\">Jacob Collier</a> to jam with his melodica on a medley of Concierto de Aranjuez and Corea’s classic original Spain. Collier played discreetly and looked a little awed, but the elder statesman warmly embraced him as a hot recruit to the musical art of jumping in the deep end. </p> <ul> <li><em>Chick Corea and the Vigil are at Ronnie Scott’s, London, tonight. <a draggable=\"true\" href=\"http://www.ronniescotts.co.uk/performances/view/2900-chick-corea-and-the-vigil-w-tim-garland-carlitos-del-puerto-marcus-gilmore-charles-altura-lui\">Box office: 020-7439 0747</a>. </em><em>Jacob Collier is at the <a href=\"http://www.efglondonjazzfestival.org.uk/\">London jazz festival</a> on 20 November. <a href=\"http://www.barbican.org.uk/music/event-detail.asp?id=18357\">Box office: 020</a></em><em><a href=\"http://www.barbican.org.uk/music/event-detail.asp?id=18357\">-7638 8891</a>.</em></li> </ul>","internalOctopusCode":"10970227","productionOffice":"UK","newspaperEditionDate":"2015-11-12T00:00:00Z","hasStoryPackage":"false","internalPageCode":"2405163","internalRevision":"370","internalContentCode":"458367570","publication":"The Guardian","trailText":"One of jazz’s most inventive piano improvisers jacks up the excitement with a dynamic rhythm section and plenty of gleeful percussive banter","allowUgc":"false","starRating":"4","headline":"Chic