 to the presence among the crew of the Enterprise of “a Scot called McCoy”. Dr McCoy was American; the Scottish character was the chief engineer Montgomery “Scotty” Scott (<a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/culture/2015/nov/07/star-trek-to-live-long-with-a-new-tv-series\" title=\"\">How the starship Enterprise and its crew lived long and prospered</a>, 7 November, page 15).</p> <p>• In an article about the phasing out of pantry cars on Indian railways, we overstated their output in saying their workers had “toiled over many decades to provide trillions of meals to billions of passengers”. But they have, over the years, provided billions of meals to passengers (<a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/nov/05/indian-railways-signal-end-of-an-era-with-plan-to-phase-out-pantry-car\" title=\"\">Indian railways’ new line: e-catering instead of pantry cars</a>, 6 November, page 26).</p>","internalOctopusCode":"10969033","productionOffice":"UK","newspaperEditionDate":"2015-11-12T00:00:00Z","hasStoryPackage":"false","internalPageCode":"2405568","internalRevision":"12","internalContentCode":"458371129","publication":"The Guardian","trailText":"Genesis housing association | Star Trek | Indian railways","allowUgc":"false","headline":"Corrections and clarifications","byline":"Corrections and clarifications column editor","commentable":"false","firstPublicationDate":"2015-11-11T21:00:02Z","isPremoderated":"false","internalComposerCode":"5643849be4b04096fed8b523","newspaperPageNumber":"44","standfirst":"Genesis housing association | Star Trek | Indian railways","creationDate":"2015-11-11T18:10:35Z","showInRelatedContent":"true","lastModified":"2015-11-11T22:00:54.022Z","legallySensitive":"false"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/news/2015/nov/11/corrections-and-clarifications","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/news/2015/nov/11/corrections-and-clarifications","sectionName":"News","elements":[],"tags":[{"id":"theguardian/mainsection/editorialsandreply","webTitle